# TikTok cookies — required to list and download videos
#
# TikTok requires a logged-in session. Export your browser cookies here.
# The file must be in Netscape/Mozilla format (all methods below produce this).
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  OPTION 1 — Browser extension (easiest, no tools needed)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#   Chrome:  Install "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" from the Chrome Web Store
#   Firefox: Install "cookies.txt" from Firefox Add-ons
#
#   1. Make sure you are logged in to https://www.tiktok.com
#   2. Click the extension icon on the TikTok tab
#   3. Click "Export" → save the file as  backend/cookies.txt
#   4. Restart the backend
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  OPTION 2 — Command line (browser must be fully closed first)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#   Requires yt-dlp to be installed:  pip install yt-dlp
#
#   Close Chrome completely, then run:
#
#     yt-dlp --cookies-from-browser chrome \
#            --cookies-to-file backend/cookies.txt \
#            "https://www.tiktok.com/" --skip-download
#
#   Replace "chrome" with firefox / edge / safari as needed.
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  NOTES
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  • Cookies expire after a few weeks — re-export if downloads fail.
#  • Never commit cookies.txt to source control (it's your TikTok session).
#  • Add  cookies.txt  to your .gitignore file.
